{
  "zh": "请仅输出且仅输出一个工具调用块，使用 Sentra XML 协议格式：\n<sentra-tools>\n  <invoke name=\"{{name}}\">\n    <parameter name=\"foo\"><string>value</string></parameter>\n    <parameter name=\"count\"><number>42</number></parameter>\n    <parameter name=\"enabled\"><boolean>true</boolean></parameter>\n    <parameter name=\"tags\">\n      <array>\n        <string>tag1</string>\n        <string>tag2</string>\n      </array>\n    </parameter>\n    <parameter name=\"config\">\n      <object>\n        <parameter name=\"k\">\n          <string>v</string>\n        </parameter>\n      </object>\n    </parameter>\n  </invoke>\n</sentra-tools>\n\n参数类型规范（仅限以下 XML 标签）：\n- <string>...</string>：字符串（任意文本，保留空格、换行和特殊字符）\n- <number>...</number>：数字（整数或小数）\n- <boolean>true/false</boolean>：布尔值\n- <null></null>：空值\n- <array>...</array>：数组；内部元素只能是 string/number/boolean/null/array/object 这六种类型之一\n- <object>...</object>：对象；内部只能包含 <parameter name=\"字段名\">VALUE</parameter>，其中 VALUE 必须是上述六种类型之一\n\n推荐用法：\n- 简单标量参数（字符串/数字/布尔/空）优先使用对应的类型标签（如 <string>、<number>），避免直接塞一整段 JSON 字符串。\n- 复杂结构（对象/数组）必须使用 <object>/<array> 结构，不要直接在 <parameter> 中放未标注类型的 JSON 文本。\n- 每个 <array> 内部只能直接包含上述六类标签，禁止嵌入其他任意标签（如 <item>、<value> 等），以便解析器安全解析（parseXmlArray 已严格按此约束实现）。\n\nCRITICAL: 在 <sentra-tools> 工具调用块中，参数值中的特殊字符必须进行标准 XML 转义（特别是 <、>、&、\"、'）。\n- 正确: <parameter name=\"html\"><string>&lt;div class=\"card\"&gt;内容&lt;/div&gt;</string></parameter>\n- 错误: <parameter name=\"html\"><string><div class=\"card\">内容</div></string></parameter>\n\n系统在解析 <sentra-tools> 时会自动将这些 XML 实体还原为原始字符再传递给工具，因此你必须在工具调用中输出合法的 XML，而不是包含未转义 <div> 等标签的半结构文本。\n\n工具调用时，你必须严格遵守上述 XML 结构，不要输出多余的文本、注释或额外的 <sentra-tools> 块。\n\n常见错误（禁止这样做）：\n- 使用 <property name=\"...\"> 标签定义对象字段（已经废弃），必须使用 <parameter name=\"...\">。\n- 在同一个 <invoke> 中为同一个名称重复输出多个 <parameter>，会导致参数覆盖或解析混乱。\n- 在 <sentra-tools> 外围输出任何自然语言解释、Markdown 或注释。\n- 在 <string> 中直接写未转义的 <div> 或其他标签，导致 XML 结构损坏。\n\n复杂示例（嵌套对象与数组）：\n<sentra-tools>\n  <invoke name=\"demo_tool\">\n    <parameter name=\"filters\">\n      <object>\n        <parameter name=\"cities\">\n          <array>\n            <string>北京</string>\n            <string>上海</string>\n          </array>\n        </parameter>\n        <parameter name=\"options\">\n          <object>\n            <parameter name=\"include_history\"><boolean>true</boolean></parameter>\n            <parameter name=\"limit\"><number>20</number></parameter>\n          </object>\n        </parameter>\n      </object>\n    </parameter>\n  </invoke>\n</sentra-tools>\n\nSchema 提示（供你理解参数含义与必填字段，不需要原样复制）：\n{{schema}}\n\n{{req_hint}}",
  "en": "Output ONE AND ONLY ONE tool call block using the Sentra XML Protocol format:\n<sentra-tools>\n  <invoke name=\"{{name}}\">\n    <parameter name=\"foo\"><string>value</string></parameter>\n    <parameter name=\"count\"><number>42</number></parameter>\n    <parameter name=\"enabled\"><boolean>true</boolean></parameter>\n    <parameter name=\"tags\">\n      <array>\n        <string>tag1</string>\n        <string>tag2</string>\n      </array>\n    </parameter>\n    <parameter name=\"config\">\n      <object>\n        <parameter name=\"k\">\n          <string>v</string>\n        </parameter>\n      </object>\n    </parameter>\n  </invoke>\n</sentra-tools>\n\nValue type specification (ONLY the following XML nodes are allowed inside parameters):\n- <string>...</string>: string (arbitrary text, keep spaces/newlines/special chars)\n- <number>...</number>: numeric value (integer or float)\n- <boolean>true/false</boolean>: boolean\n- <null></null>: null\n- <array>...</array>: array; its direct children MUST be one of string/number/boolean/null/array/object only\n- <object>...</object>: object; its content MUST consist of <parameter name=\"field\">VALUE</parameter> where VALUE is one of the six types above\n\nRecommended usage:\n- For simple scalar parameters (string/number/boolean/null), prefer explicit type tags (<string>, <number>, etc.) instead of embedding raw JSON.\n- For complex structures (objects/arrays), you MUST use <object>/<array> with typed children, instead of placing a whole JSON blob directly in <parameter>.\n- Inside every <array>, only the six node types listed above are allowed; DO NOT introduce other tags (such as <item> or <value>). The parser (parseXmlArray) relies on this constraint for safe decoding.\n\nCRITICAL: Inside <sentra-tools> blocks, you MUST XML-escape special characters (<, >, &, \" and ') in parameter values to produce well-formed XML.\n- CORRECT: <parameter name=\"html\"><string>&lt;div class=\"card\"&gt;content&lt;/div&gt;</string></parameter>\n- INCORRECT: <parameter name=\"html\"><string><div class=\"card\">content</div></string></parameter>\n\nThe system will automatically unescape these XML entities back to the original characters before passing arguments to tools, so you MUST focus on emitting valid XML rather than semi-structured text with raw <div> tags embedded inside values.\n\nYou MUST strictly follow the XML structure above for tool calls. Do not output extra text, comments, or additional <sentra-tools> blocks.\n\nCommon mistakes (DO NOT do this):\n- Using <property name=\"...\"> to define object fields (deprecated); you MUST use <parameter name=\"...\"> instead.\n- Emitting multiple <parameter> elements with the same name in a single <invoke>, which leads to overwriting or ambiguous arguments.\n- Writing any natural language explanation, Markdown, or comments outside the <sentra-tools> block.\n- Placing raw <div> or other tags inside <string> without XML-escaping, which breaks XML structure.\n\nComplex example (nested objects and arrays):\n<sentra-tools>\n  <invoke name=\"demo_tool\">\n    <parameter name=\"filters\">\n      <object>\n        <parameter name=\"cities\">\n          <array>\n            <string>Beijing</string>\n            <string>Shanghai</string>\n          </array>\n        </parameter>\n        <parameter name=\"options\">\n          <object>\n            <parameter name=\"include_history\"><boolean>true</boolean></parameter>\n            <parameter name=\"limit\"><number>20</number></parameter>\n          </object>\n        </parameter>\n      </object>\n    </parameter>\n  </invoke>\n</sentra-tools>\n\nSchema hint (for understanding parameter meanings and required fields, you do NOT need to copy it verbatim):\n{{schema}}\n\n{{req_hint}}"
}
